00:12:40,794 --> 00:12:43,077
-你为他骄傲吧  -非常  老爷
-Proud of him? -Very, my lord.

177
00:12:43,546 --> 00:12:44,735
很对
Quite right too.

178
00:12:46,591 --> 00:12:47,915
很高兴你能来到这里
Glad to have you with us.

179
00:12:48,259 --> 00:12:49,417
谢谢  老爷
Thank you, my lord.

180
00:12:53,056 --> 00:12:56,007
今天正餐是什么时候  下午2点  4点
What are we at dinner tonight? 14:00? 16:00?

181
00:12:56,184 --> 00:12:57,206
中午12点  老爷
Twelve, sir.

182
00:12:57,477 --> 00:12:58,259
很好
Right.

183
00:12:59,896 --> 00:13:01,001
谢谢  老爷
Thank you, my lord.

184
00:13:29,551 --> 00:13:32,222
这只水壶我不知道该放哪儿
This pitcher seems out of place here.

185
00:13:32,223 --> 00:13:34,003
饭厅  当心别碰坏
Dining room. Well spotted.

186
00:13:43,189 --> 00:13:46,516
-你好  威廉  -日安  肯顿小姐
-Hello, William, how are you? -Good day, Miss Kenton.

187
00:14:29,486 --> 00:14:33,229
我想这些能为你的会客厅增添一份光彩
I thought these might brighten your parlour.

188
00:14:33,573 --> 00:14:34,762
您说什么
Beg your pardon?

189
00:14:35,742 --> 00:14:38,276
它们能给你带来好心情
They might cheer things up for you.

190
00:14:38,369 --> 00:14:40,236
您真好心
That's very kind of you.

191
00:14:43,041 --> 00:14:45,710
如果您愿意  我可以多采一些来
If you like, I could bring in some more for you.

192
00:14:46,002 --> 00:14:47,410
谢谢
Thank you

193
00:14:48,171 --> 00:14:51,664
但是我把这间屋子当作私人工作室
but I regard this room as my private place of work

194
00:14:51,925 --> 00:14:54,834
希望尽量少摆设一些让我分心的东西
and I prefer to keep distractions to a minimum.

195
00:14:55,053 --> 00:14:57,920
您怎么会认为这些花会让您分心呢
Would you call flowers a distraction, then?

196
00:14:58,181 --> 00:15:01,507
我感谢您的好意  屋子还是保持原样为好
I appreciate your kindness. I prefer to keep things as they are.

197
00:15:01,810 --> 00:15:06,429
既然你在这儿了  有件事我想对您说
But since you are here, there is a small matter I wanted to mention.

198
00:15:06,523 --> 00:15:10,183
昨天早上我正巧从厨房经过
I happened to be walking past the kitchen yesterday morning

199
00:15:10,485 --> 00:15:13,050
听到你叫某人"威廉"
and I heard you call to someone named William.

200
00:15:13,321 --> 00:15:16,689
请问您是在称呼哪位
May I ask who you were addressing by that name?

201
00:15:17,992 --> 00:15:20,818
我应该是在称呼您父亲
I should think I was addressing your father.

202
00:15:21,704 --> 00:15:24,030
这里没有其他人叫威廉
There are no other Williams in this house.

203
00:15:24,249 --> 00:15:25,198
是这样
True.

204
00:15:26,334 --> 00:15:29,952
请您以后称呼我父亲"史蒂文斯先生"
May I ask you in future to address my father as Mr. Stevens?

205
00:15:30,505 --> 00:15:33,623
如果是在对下属提到他时  你可以称他
If speaking of him to a third party, you may call him

206
00:15:33,800 --> 00:15:36,417
史蒂文斯一世  作为与称呼我的区别
Mr. Stevens Sr. to distinguish him from myself.

207
00:15:36,719 --> 00:15:40,411
我会很感激您这么做的  肯顿小姐
So I would be most grateful to you, Miss Kenton.

208
00:15:41,766 --> 00:15:45,176
我不是很理解您的意思
I don't quite understand what you're getting at.

209
00:15:45,770 --> 00:15:50,389
我是这里的女管家  您父亲是副男管家
I am the housekeeper in this house, and your father is the under-butler.

210
00:15:50,734 --> 00:15:55,186
我习惯用下属的名字来称呼他们
I am accustomed to addressing under-servants by their Christian names.

211
00:15:56,656 --> 00:16:00,733
请先停下  听我说
If you would stop to think for a moment, you'd realize

212
00:16:00,910 --> 00:16:04,904
像您这样用名字直接称呼我父亲
how inappropriate it is for one such as yourself to address as William

213
00:16:05,165 --> 00:16:07,532
是极为不合适的
someone such as my father.

214
00:16:08,209 --> 00:16:12,995
想必您父亲一定觉得很难堪
It must have been very galling for your father to be called William

215
00:16:13,256 --> 00:16:15,331
像我这样身份的人直呼其名
by one such as myself.

216
00:16:15,383 --> 00:16:17,750
我想说的是  如果您仔细观察
My father is a person from whom

217
00:16:18,094 --> 00:16:21,254
您将从他身上学到不少东西
if you'd observe him more, you may learn things.

218
00:16:21,514 --> 00:16:24,131
我很感激您的建议  但请一定要告诉我
I'm grateful for your advice, but do tell me

219
00:16:24,434 --> 00:16:26,509
我能从他那儿学到什么
what things might I learn from him?

220
00:16:26,811 --> 00:16:28,886
请允许我指出一点
I might point out that you're

221
00:16:29,063 --> 00:16:31,848
您还不是很熟悉一些物品的摆放位置和用途
often unsure of what goes where and which item is which.

222
00:16:34,110 --> 00:16:37,311
我确信史蒂文斯一世精于他的工作职责
I'm sure Mr. Stevens Sr. is very good at his job

223
00:16:37,781 --> 00:16:41,149
但我也向您保证  我也对于自己的工作十分擅长
but I can assure you that I'm very good at mine.

224
00:16:41,409 --> 00:16:42,431
-当然  -谢谢
-Of course. -Thank you.

225
00:16:42,660 --> 00:16:44,569
请允许我先告辞了
If you will please excuse me.

226
00:16:49,459 --> 00:16:50,283
好吧
Oh, well.

227
00:16:58,635 --> 00:17:00,710
向我们的厨师致意
My compliments to cook.

228
00:17:01,179 --> 00:17:03,129
多么美味的脆皮
What a lovely piece of crackling.

229
00:17:04,682 --> 00:17:09,802
你好像说了些有趣的话  跟大家分享一下吧
I'm sure you said something witty. Share it with the rest of us.

230
00:17:10,355 --> 00:17:13,295
我说这些青豆做的很棒  我很喜欢
I said the sprouts is done the way I like them.

231
00:17:13,296 --> 00:17:14,765
很干脆  没有太硬
Crisp-like, not mushy.

232
00:17:14,818 --> 00:17:17,059
应该是很"松脆"  不是很"干脆"
Sprouts "are" done, not " is" done.

233
00:17:17,779 --> 00:17:18,853
对吧  乔治
Isn't that right, George?

234
00:17:18,947 --> 00:17:19,969
是的  史蒂文斯先生
Yes, Mr. Stevens.

235
00:17:20,240 --> 00:17:24,150
抱歉纠正你的用词  因为我在你这年纪
Forgive the correction, as I would have done

236
00:17:24,202 --> 00:17:27,028
十分注重养成自己的言语得当
at your age for the sake of my education.

237
00:17:27,288 --> 00:17:31,616
我相信你也和其他人一样有志于升职
I'm sure even you have ambitions to rise in your profession.

238
00:17:31,876 --> 00:17:35,703
是的  我也想成为一个管家  被称呼为某某先生
Oh, yes. I want to be a butler, to be called Mister

239
00:17:36,047 --> 00:17:38,940
坐在自己的小客厅  有自己的壁炉
sit in my own pantry by my own fire,

240
00:17:38,941 --> 00:17:39,905
嘴上叼着雪茄
smoking my cigar.

241
00:17:40,260 --> 00:17:43,711
你知道要成为一个优秀的管家最重要的是什么
I wonder if you realize what it takes to be a great butler?

242
00:17:43,972 --> 00:17:46,297
保持庄重  处乱不惊
Takes dignity, that's what it takes.

243
00:17:46,808 --> 00:17:50,749
谢谢  史蒂文斯先生  重点是要处乱不惊
Thank you, Mr. Stevens. Dignity, that's right. Dignity.

244
00:17:51,938 --> 00:17:55,431
绅士中的绅士  这本杂志上给出的定义是这样
The definition from our quarterly The Gentlemen's Gentleman:

245
00:17:55,692 --> 00:17:58,226
优秀的管家必须要做到超乎想象的处乱不惊
A great butler must be possessed of dignity-

246
00:17:58,528 --> 00:18:00,645
才能保住他的职位
In keeping with his position.

247
00:18:02,741 --> 00:18:05,858
曾经在印度有一个英国管家
There was this English butler in India.

248
00:18:06,786 --> 00:18:11,322
一天他走到饭厅里  发现有什么东西在桌子下
One day, he goes in the dining room and what's under the table?

249
00:18:11,583 --> 00:18:12,573
一只老虎
A tiger.

250
00:18:13,710 --> 00:18:17,328
他面不改色地走到客厅
Not turning a hair, he goes to the drawing room.

251
00:18:19,174 --> 00:18:20,761
打扰您  老爷
Excuse me, my lord.

252
00:18:20,762 --> 00:18:23,584
为了不打扰在场的女士  他轻声说
And whispering, so as not to upset the ladies:

253
00:18:24,512 --> 00:18:27,755
餐厅里有只老虎
" I'm sorry. There appears to be a tiger in the dining room.

254
00:18:28,433 --> 00:18:32,510
请允许我用枪射杀它
Perhaps His Lordship will permit use of the twelve-bores?"

255
00:18:34,063 --> 00:18:38,724
他们继续用着茶  突然  三声枪响
They go on drinking their tea. And then, there's three gunshots.

256
00:18:39,319 --> 00:18:41,098
他们谁也没觉得奇怪
They don't think nothing of it.

257
00:18:41,099 --> 00:18:43,688
在印度  人们对什么事都习以为常
In India, they're used to anything.

258
00:18:44,449 --> 00:18:47,650
当管家回来帮他们的茶续杯时
When the butler is back to refresh the teapots

259
00:18:48,369 --> 00:18:50,528
他十分镇定地说道
he says, cool as a cucumber:

260
00:18:50,705 --> 00:18:53,990
老爷  午餐将按时开始
" Dinner will be served at the usual time, my lord.

261
00:18:54,417 --> 00:18:58,703
我也向您保证  到时餐厅里会跟往常一样
And I am pleased to say there will be no discernible traces left

262
00:18:59,005 --> 00:19:02,206
不会留下任何异样的痕迹
of the recent occurrence by that time. "

263
00:19:04,427 --> 00:19:08,171
这句话  "到时餐厅里会跟往常一样"
I'll repeat it. "There will be no discernible traces left

264
00:19:08,431 --> 00:19:12,206
"不会留下任何异样的痕迹"
of the recent occurrence by that time. "

265
00:19:13,645 --> 00:19:15,064
很精彩  史蒂文斯先生
Wonderful, Mr. Stevens.

266
00:19:15,065 --> 00:19:16,179
谢谢  史蒂文斯先生
Thank you, Mr. Stevens.

267
00:19:16,481 --> 00:19:17,852
精彩的故事
Wonderful story.

268
00:19:17,853 --> 00:19:21,184
我们都该努力做到这一点  处乱不惊
That's the ideal that we should all aim for. Dignity.

269
00:19:24,322 --> 00:19:25,396
找您的  史蒂文斯先生
For you, Mr. Stevens.

270
00:19:26,157 --> 00:19:27,148
谢谢
Thank you.

271
00:19:27,200 --> 00:19:29,901
是找史蒂文斯先生一世的  史蒂文斯先生
It's for Mr. Stevens Sr., Mr. Stevens.

272
00:19:30,370 --> 00:19:32,403
谢谢  肯顿小姐
Thank you, Miss Kenton.

273
00:19:34,499 --> 00:19:37,658
玛丽  把他的盘子放到厨师那里去保温
Put Mr. Stevens Sr. 's plate with cook to keep it warm.

274
00:19:37,919 --> 00:19:39,160
是  肯顿小姐
Yes, Miss Kenton.

275
00:19:41,005 --> 00:19:41,787
谢谢您  肯顿小姐
Thank you.

276
00:19:42,132 --> 00:19:43,915
不用谢  史蒂文斯先生
Not at all, Mr. Stevens.

277
00:21:16,851 --> 00:21:20,386
史蒂文斯先生  我看到您的扫帚在外面地上
If you're searching for your dustpan, it is out on the landing.

278
00:21:20,730 --> 00:21:21,679
我的扫帚
My dustpan?

279
00:21:21,898 --> 00:21:24,265
您把它放地上了
You've left it on the landing.

280
00:21:24,567 --> 00:21:26,218
我没用过扫帚
I haven't used a dustpan.

281
00:21:26,219 --> 00:21:28,603
是吗  那么也许是别人的
Really? It must be somebody else.

282
00:21:28,905 --> 00:21:30,429
我不明白你的意思
I don't follow you.

283
00:21:30,430 --> 00:21:32,231
是我弄错了  脑子不好使
My mistake, no doubt. One of many.

284
00:21:38,915 --> 00:21:40,072
早上好  先生
Morning, sir.

285
00:21:51,678 --> 00:21:55,046
我邀请了杜邦作为会议上法国的代表
I've invited Giscard Dupont D'Ivry as the French delegate.

286
00:21:55,265 --> 00:21:56,839
他才不会来
He'll never come!

287
00:21:57,100 --> 00:21:59,634
他保证说会来的
I just had word of his acceptance.

288
00:21:59,936 --> 00:22:04,931
杜邦十分针对德国  他在33年日内瓦的演说
Dupont is fanatically anti-German. His speech in Geneva in 33'

289
00:22:05,191 --> 00:22:07,861
让我都汗颜与法国站在同一战线
made me ashamed to be an ally of the French.

290
00:22:08,194 --> 00:22:09,852
这绝不是我们英国人的做派
It's not the English way.

291
00:22:10,029 --> 00:22:11,020
当然
No, it is not.

292
00:22:11,364 --> 00:22:13,202
我们这次会议的目的
This is the purpose of our conference,

293
00:22:13,203 --> 00:22:15,858
就是要非正式地讨论国际局势
to discuss these matters informally

294
00:22:16,119 --> 00:22:19,153
绝不是那种国际化的死气沉沉的会议
far from the to-do of an international conference

295
00:22:19,247 --> 00:22:21,489
而是友好地  放松地
in the friendly and relaxed

296
00:22:22,375 --> 00:22:24,742
聚在某个人的家里
atmosphere of one's home.

297
00:22:26,045 --> 00:22:28,830
我们可以说服法国人接受我们的观点
We may bring round the French to our point of view.

298
00:22:29,132 --> 00:22:31,040
对德国人也是一样
And that of the Germans.

299
00:22:31,384 --> 00:22:35,837
不过我插一句  我们怎样来联合德国人
I'm sorry to interrupt, but how can we associate with the Germans?

300
00:22:35,930 --> 00:22:40,091
那可是纳粹  他们撕毁协议又践踏公约
With the Nazi Party! They have torn up and trampled every treaty

301
00:22:40,268 --> 00:22:42,884
对欧洲来说是日渐增长的威胁
and are a growing threat to Europe,

302
00:22:42,885 --> 00:22:44,804
更别说德国的独裁统治了
not to mention a brutal dictatorship.

303
00:22:45,190 --> 00:22:50,257
年轻人  我也曾去过柏林
My dear boy, when I was in Berlin, I saw at last a happy German people

304
00:22:50,695 --> 00:22:54,981
看到的是衣食无忧  热爱自己国家和元首的普通人
with jobs, bread, pride in their country and love of their leader.

305
00:22:55,283 --> 00:22:57,150
那么犹太人呢
And what about the Jews?

306
00:23:03,583 --> 00:23:07,524
史蒂文斯先生  老爷说要把陈列室里的中国人像
Did His Lordship wish to exchange the Chinaman in the cabinet room

307
00:23:07,879 --> 00:23:09,579
放到大厅里来吗
with the one outside the door?

308
00:23:10,131 --> 00:23:11,497
-中国人像   -是的
-Chinaman? -Yes.

309
00:23:11,800 --> 00:23:15,066
原本在陈列室的中国人像就在门外大厅里
The Chinaman from the cabinet room is outside this door.

310
00:23:15,067 --> 00:23:16,210
您自己去看一下
See for yourself.

311
00:23:16,763 --> 00:23:18,462
我现在很忙
I'm busy at the moment.

312
00:23:19,265 --> 00:23:22,758
就把头伸出去您亲自看一下
Just pop your head outside this door and see for yourself.

313
00:23:22,852 --> 00:23:27,013
-我等会再去看  -您以为我在胡诌
-I'll look into the matter later. -You think it's a fantasy?

314
00:23:27,273 --> 00:23:30,099
因为我缺乏经验所以就胡诌了吗
A fantasy on my part due to my inexperience?

315
00:23:30,235 --> 00:23:33,811
我在这里的事还没忙完  肯顿小姐
I'm busy in this room, Miss Kenton.

316
00:23:34,072 --> 00:23:35,344
那我等着
I shall wait.

317
00:23:36,408 --> 00:23:37,429
就在门外
Outside.

318
00:24:40,346 --> 00:24:41,128
看
Look!

319
00:24:41,473 --> 00:24:44,257
-那不是原来在那儿的人像  -我很忙
-Is that not the wrong Chinaman? -I am very busy.

320
00:24:44,601 --> 00:24:46,968
您难道没有别的事可做了吗
Have you nothing better to do than stand around?

321
00:24:47,270 --> 00:24:49,387
您看一下  跟我说实话
Look at it and tell me the truth.

322
00:24:49,481 --> 00:24:50,614
把声音放轻点
Keep your voice down.

323
00:24:50,615 --> 00:24:52,598
其他佣人看到我们因为一个人像
What would the other servants think

324
00:24:52,942 --> 00:24:55,184
而大肆争吵  会怎么想
of us shouting about a Chinaman?

325
00:24:55,528 --> 00:24:57,228
那么我就请您
And I would ask you

326
00:24:57,530 --> 00:25:01,149
转过身  看一看那个人像
to turn around and look at the Chinaman.

327
00:25:07,082 --> 00:25:08,614
只是犯了个小错而已
It is a small mistake.

328
00:25:08,917 --> 00:25:12,326
您父亲的工作量超过了他的年纪所能承受的
Your father is entrusted with more than he can cope with.

329
00:25:12,378 --> 00:25:13,744
让我过去
Let me pass.

330
00:25:14,047 --> 00:25:16,831
是您父亲把扫帚放在了楼梯上
Your father left the dustpan on the floor.

331
00:25:17,175 --> 00:25:19,959
他忘记了磨刀具  又把人像搞错了
He left polish on the cutlery and confused the Chinaman.

332
00:25:20,303 --> 00:25:22,753
在他犯下大错之前  你要认清现状
Recognize this before he commits a major error!

333
00:25:22,931 --> 00:25:25,270
您不能用这种语气跟我说话
You can't talk to me like this.

334
00:25:25,271 --> 00:25:26,674
恐怕我不得不这样
I'm afraid I must.

335
00:25:26,935 --> 00:25:29,218
我是在给您提建议
I'm giving you serious advice.

336
00:25:29,771 --> 00:25:33,890
为了他的健康  必须得给他减轻一些工作量
Your father should be relieved of a number of his duties for his own good.

337
00:25:35,068 --> 00:25:36,916
不论他曾经多么能干
Whatever he once was,

338
00:25:36,917 --> 00:25:39,437
他现在已经没有那份精力和体力了
he no longer has the same ability or strength.

339
00:25:40,365 --> 00:25:42,648
我感谢您的建议
I thank you for your advice.

340
00:25:42,992 --> 00:25:44,942
现在我要继续做我的事了
Perhaps now I can go about my business.

341
00:25:45,245 --> 00:25:47,778
我从没想过要打扰您做事
