368
00:27:27,889 --> 00:27:29,964
你父亲好些了吗
Your father feeling better?

369
00:27:30,141 --> 00:27:32,049
他完全恢复了  老爷
He's made a full recovery.

370
00:27:32,102 --> 00:27:33,676
很好
Good.

371
00:27:33,937 --> 00:27:37,972
我们都不希望那样的事再发生  对吧
We don't wish to see anything of that sort ever happen again, do we?

372
00:27:38,274 --> 00:27:40,060
我是指你父亲摔倒这事
I mean, your father collapsing.

373
00:27:40,061 --> 00:27:41,434
确实是这样  老爷
Indeed not, my lord.

374
00:27:41,611 --> 00:27:43,811
而且无论何时  无论何地
And it could happen anywhere.

375
00:27:44,572 --> 00:27:46,022
都可能发生
At any time.

376
00:27:47,242 --> 00:27:51,277
听着  第一位外国代表将在两周内到达
The first of the foreign delegates will be here in less than a fortnight.

377
00:27:51,579 --> 00:27:53,590
我们都做了充分的准备  老爷
We are well prepared, my lord.

378
00:27:53,591 --> 00:27:54,655
我毫不怀疑这一点
I'm sure you are.

379
00:27:54,958 --> 00:27:57,783
在这里发生的事情将
What happens within this house could have

380
00:27:58,086 --> 00:28:01,245
对整个欧洲的命运产生影响
considerable repercussions on the course that Europe takes.

381
00:28:02,090 --> 00:28:03,623
这件事意义重大
It means a great deal.

382
00:28:03,883 --> 00:28:07,084
对于我个人来讲也是十分重要
And it means a great deal to me personally.

383
00:28:07,512 --> 00:28:11,756
我有个德国朋友  卡尔?汉斯
I had a German friend, Karl-Heinz Bremann.

384
00:28:12,100 --> 00:28:14,800
我们在战时属于敌对的两边
We fought on opposite sides in the war.

385
00:28:15,061 --> 00:28:17,233
但是我们约定  等战争结束
We always said when it was over,

386
00:28:17,234 --> 00:28:18,971
可以一起坐下来好好喝一杯
we'd sit down and have a drink

387
00:28:19,149 --> 00:28:20,515
像普通人一样
like gentlemen.

388
00:28:22,360 --> 00:28:25,029
但是凡尔赛条约却让我无颜以对
The Versailles Treaty made a liar of me.

389
00:28:25,822 --> 00:28:28,356
无颜以对  史蒂文斯
Yes, a liar, Stevens.

390
00:28:28,658 --> 00:28:31,173
因为盟军制订的那些制裁条款太过猛烈
Because the terms we imposed were so harsh

391
00:28:31,174 --> 00:28:33,027
以至于整个国家的经济行将崩塌
that Germany was finished.

392
00:28:33,913 --> 00:28:35,738
对于战败国来说  不应该是这样的
One doesn't do that to a defeated foe.

393
00:28:36,082 --> 00:28:39,367
一旦举白旗投降  就应该全部都结束
Once your man's on the canvas, it ought to be over.

394
00:28:40,253 --> 00:28:43,996
我那个德国朋友  被通货膨胀给害惨了
My friend Bremann was ruined by inflation.

395
00:28:44,674 --> 00:28:47,542
在战后的德国连一份工作都找不到
Couldn't get a job in postwar Germany.

396
00:28:48,511 --> 00:28:49,783
于是自杀了
Killed himself.

397
00:28:51,264 --> 00:28:54,841
在一节火车车厢里开枪自杀了
Shot himself in a railway carriage.

398
00:28:55,810 --> 00:29:00,221
从那时候起  我便觉得有义务帮助德国并
Since then, I've felt it my duty to help Germany and to give her

399
00:29:00,565 --> 00:29:01,806
给这个国家公平的对待
a fair chance.

400
00:29:02,067 --> 00:29:04,100
所以这场会议非常的关键
So this conference is crucial

401
00:29:04,402 --> 00:29:07,979
不能有任何的意外来打乱会议的秩序
and we can't run the risk of any accidents.

402
00:29:08,156 --> 00:29:10,314
你父亲可以不用离开
There's no question of your father leaving.

403
00:29:11,201 --> 00:29:13,526
你只要重新安排一下他的工作就行
You're simply being asked to reconsider his duties.

404
00:29:13,870 --> 00:29:16,612
当然  老爷  我完全明白
Of course, my lord. I understand fully.

405
00:29:16,998 --> 00:29:17,989
很好
Good.

406
00:29:18,833 --> 00:29:21,742
那这事就交给你了  史蒂文斯
I'll leave you to think about it, then, Stevens.

407
00:29:22,045 --> 00:29:23,067
谢谢  老爷
Thank you, sir.

408
00:30:28,278 --> 00:30:32,897
餐厅里缺人手  需要你到备餐室帮忙
I'm short-handed in the dining room. I can use you in the servery.

409
00:30:33,199 --> 00:30:36,609
-谢谢  史蒂文斯先生  -表现机灵点
-Thank you, Mr. Stevens, sir. -Smarten up. Look sharp.

410
00:30:44,961 --> 00:30:45,952
早上好
Good morning.

411
00:30:46,337 --> 00:30:47,443
早上好
Good morning.

412
00:30:51,801 --> 00:30:54,877
我猜你肯定早起准备工作了
I might've known you'd be up and ready for the day.

413
00:30:55,180 --> 00:30:57,380
我已经起床两个小时了
I've been up for two hours.

414
00:30:58,016 --> 00:30:59,679
那样睡眠会不足
That's not much sleep.

415
00:30:59,680 --> 00:31:01,676
对于我  这些时间够了
It's all the sleep I need.

416
00:31:04,022 --> 00:31:06,347
我来跟你谈一谈
I've come to talk to you.

417
00:31:06,649 --> 00:31:09,851
说吧  我有一上午的时间
Talk, then. I haven't got all morning.

418
00:31:09,986 --> 00:31:13,396
-那我直说了  -那你就快说吧
-I'll come straight to the point. -Do, and be done with it.

419
00:31:13,656 --> 00:31:16,221
你还有好些事要做
Some of us have work to be getting on with.

420
00:31:18,411 --> 00:31:23,322
下周这里要举办一个很重要的国际会议
There's to be a very important conference in this house next week.

421
00:31:23,541 --> 00:31:27,076
各国的政要都会来这里作客
People of great stature will be His Lordship's guests.

422
00:31:27,587 --> 00:31:29,787
我们必须要做到万无一失
We must all put our best foot forward.

423
00:31:31,508 --> 00:31:34,292
鉴于父亲您最近的意外
Because of Father's recent accident

424
00:31:34,636 --> 00:31:38,327
建议您不用再端盘子服侍用餐了
it has been suggested that you no longer wait at table.

425
00:31:42,811 --> 00:31:46,179
我每天当男仆服侍用餐
I've waited at table every day

426
00:31:46,481 --> 00:31:49,046
已经做了54年了
for the last 54 years.

427
00:31:51,236 --> 00:31:54,896
您以后也不用再端那些重的盘子了
It has also been decided that you should no longer carry heavy trays.

428
00:31:55,907 --> 00:31:59,025
这是一张修改过的工作清单
Now, here's a revised list of your duties.

429
00:31:59,285 --> 00:32:00,985
听着  我跌倒
Look, I fell

430
00:32:01,371 --> 00:32:03,154
是因为地上的石块不平整
because of those paving stones.

431
00:32:03,415 --> 00:32:04,489
有凸起的石块
They're crooked.

432
00:32:05,917 --> 00:32:09,410
你为何不在下一个人因此摔倒前去修整一下地面
Why don't you get them put right before someone else falls?

433
00:32:11,506 --> 00:32:15,197
您看一下修改过的工作内容
You will read the revised list of your duties.

434
00:32:15,552 --> 00:32:17,752
去把那些石块给整平了
Get those stones put right.

435
00:32:19,889 --> 00:32:23,883
你不想让那些重要人物因此摔断脖子吧
You don't want those "gentlemen of stature" breaking their necks.

436
00:32:26,271 --> 00:32:28,179
当然不
No, indeed, I don't.

437
00:32:48,001 --> 00:32:49,023
怎么了
What is it?

438
00:33:13,568 --> 00:33:16,561
接下来您的工作需要到处走
You have what we can call a roving commission.

439
00:33:16,863 --> 00:33:20,314
换种说法  就是最大限度地
In other words, you can exercise your own judgment

440
00:33:20,617 --> 00:33:22,733
自由工作
within certain limits, of course.

441
00:33:23,119 --> 00:33:26,654
这是你的拖把
Now, here are the mops, and  Here.

442
00:33:26,915 --> 00:33:29,699
-这是我的拖把  -对  这是你的刷子
-Are these me mops? -Right. Your brushes.

443
00:33:29,876 --> 00:33:31,450
这是我的刷子
And me brushes?

444
00:33:32,837 --> 00:33:35,121
-这是我的拖把  -对
-And me mops. -That's right.

445
00:33:38,051 --> 00:33:40,126
你想让我用它们做什么
What do you want me to do with them?

446
00:33:40,595 --> 00:33:43,835
我想你知道要怎么做  父亲
I think you know what to do with them, Father.

447
00:33:43,836 --> 00:33:45,131
擦灰尘和污垢
Look for dust and dirt.

448
00:33:45,809 --> 00:33:48,478
如果我发现任何的灰尘和污垢
If I find any dust or dirt

449
00:33:48,686 --> 00:33:51,137
我就用拖把解决掉
I go over them with this mop.

450
00:33:51,481 --> 00:33:52,638
对极了
That's right.

451
00:33:52,857 --> 00:33:55,766
我建议您先从
Now, I suggest you start off

452
00:33:55,944 --> 00:33:58,186
这些门把手开始
with the brasses on the doors.

453
00:33:58,530 --> 00:34:01,230
先那边的一扇门  然后是那边开着的那扇
There's that door there. Then the door that's open.

454
00:34:01,533 --> 00:34:03,649
然后那边的门
And then there's this door here

455
00:34:12,127 --> 00:34:14,494
这是你的抛光剂和除尘掸
Here's your polish. And duster.

456
00:34:15,547 --> 00:34:20,458
接下来的一些日子  这里将会创造一段历史
History could well be made under this roof over the next few days.

457
00:34:20,718 --> 00:34:22,585
你们中的每一个人
Each and every one of you

458
00:34:22,887 --> 00:34:27,006
都该为自己在这段时间中的付出感到自豪
can be proud of the role you will play on this occasion.

459
00:34:28,268 --> 00:34:31,219
想象自己身在军队的最前沿
Imagine yourself the head of a battalion

460
00:34:31,438 --> 00:34:34,347
即使你只是在往水壶倒热水
even if it is only filling the hot-water bottles.

461
00:34:35,567 --> 00:34:38,351
每个人的工作都有价值
Each one has his own particular duty

462
00:34:38,528 --> 00:34:41,604
你们各有所长的价值
or her particular duty, as the cap fits.

463
00:34:41,698 --> 00:34:43,786
给铜器抛光  把银器擦亮
Polished brass, brilliant silver,

464
00:34:43,787 --> 00:34:46,025
把红木擦得像镜子一般能映出形状
mahogany shining like a mirror.

465
00:34:46,870 --> 00:34:49,987
这是对这些外国来客最好的欢迎
That is the welcome we will show these foreign visitors

466
00:34:50,290 --> 00:34:52,448
让他们知道  这是在英国
to let them know they are in England

467
00:34:52,792 --> 00:34:56,452
在这里秩序和传统仍然是不变的主流
where order and tradition still prevail.

468
00:35:26,284 --> 00:35:27,525
谢谢  布莱恩
Thank you, Brian.

469
00:35:57,816 --> 00:36:00,183
老爷  那个美国人刘易斯先生到了
Mr. Lewis, the American, has arrived.

470
00:36:00,527 --> 00:36:03,436
